  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "FMCG Accountant",
  "description": "<p><strong>Core Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li><strong>Financial Reporting & Control:</strong> Oversee general ledger operations, ensure timely month-end/year-end closing, and prepare accurate financial statements (IFRS/local GAAP).</li><li><strong>Inventory & Costing:</strong> Manage inventory accounting, including stock take, valuation, and reconciling inventory records.</li><li><strong>Accounts Receivable/Payable:</strong> Manage high-volume vendor payments, customer collections, and AR ageing schedules.</li><li><strong>Budgeting & Analysis:</strong> Support annual budgeting and forecasting, analyzing variances in sales, costs, and profitability.</li><li><strong>Compliance:</strong> Handle GST filings, tax submissions, and coordinate with auditors. <br /><br /><strong>Required Skills and Qualifications</strong></li><li><li><strong>Education:</strong> Degree in Accounting or Finance (ACCA/CA/CPA qualification preferred).</li><li><strong>Experience:</strong> 3+ years in accounting, with preference for FMCG, retail, or manufacturing environments.</li><li><strong>Technical Skills:</strong> Advanced proficiency in Microsoft Excel (VLOOKUP, Pivot Tables) and ERP systems (e.g., SAP, Oracle).</li><li><strong>Soft Skills:</strong> Strong analytical skills, ability to work under pressure, and high attention to detail. </li></li></ul>",
